Real Madrid and Atletico Madrid have faced each other in the knockout stages of the European Cup/UEFA Champions League in five previous seasons, with Los Blancos progressing/winning on all five occasions.

Spurs have won seven of their last 11 major European matches against Dutch sides, with this their first knockout meeting since beating Ajax 3-2 in May 2019 in the second leg of the UEFA Champions League semi-final to reach the final.

Feyenoord have lost just one of their 12 home games in European competition against Italian sides, with the exception coming in a 2-1 defeat to Roma during the 2014-15 UEFA Europa League.

title: Benfica vs Barcelona - UEFA Champions League 2024/25 Round of 16 - 1st Leg

Benfica and Barcelona have already met in the UEFA Champions League this season, with nine goals being scored in an eventual 5-4 win for Barcelona. Of the 40 times that Benfica have scored 4+ goals in a European home match, that’s the only occasion when they’ve ever failed to win.
